    {
      "question": "A tangent $PQ$ at a point $P$ of a circle of radius $5 \\text{ cm}$ meets a line through the centre $O$ at a point $Q$ so that $OQ = 13 \\text{ cm}$. The length of $PQ$ is:",
      "answer": "(C)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "The radius is perpendicular to the tangent at the point of contact.",
          "In right $\\triangle OPQ$, by Pythagoras theorem, $OP^2 + PQ^2 = OQ^2$.",
          "Substitute $OP = 5$ and $OQ = 13$ to find $PQ$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$OP \\perp PQ \\Rightarrow \\triangle OPQ \\text{ is a right triangle at } P. \\\\ OP^2 + PQ^2 = OQ^2 \\\\ 5^2 + PQ^2 = 13^2 \\\\ 25 + PQ^2 = 169 \\\\ PQ^2 = 144 \\\\ PQ = 12 \\text{ cm}$"
      },
