      "question": "If tangents $PA$ and $PB$ from a point $P$ to a circle with centre $O$ are inclined to each other at an angle of $80^\\circ$, then $\\angle POA$ is equal to:",
      "answer": "(A)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "In quadrilateral $OAPB$, $\\angle OAP = \\angle OBP = 90^\\circ$.",
          "The sum of angles in a quadrilateral is $360^\\circ$.",
          "$\\angle AOB = 180^\\circ - 80^\\circ = 100^\\circ$.",
          "In $\\triangle OAP$ and $\\triangle OBP$, $\\angle POA = \\frac{1}{2} \\angle AOB$."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\angle AOB + \\angle APB = 180^\\circ \\\\ \\angle AOB + 80^\\circ = 180^\\circ \\\\ \\angle AOB = 100^\\circ \\\\ \\triangle OAP \\cong \\triangle OBP \\\\ \\angle POA = \\frac{1}{2} \\angle AOB = 50^\\circ"
      },
