    {
      "question": "The length of a tangent from a point $A$ at a distance of $5 \\text{ cm}$ from the centre of the circle is $4 \\text{ cm}$. The radius of the circle is:",
      "answer": "(B)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Let the radius be $r$.",
          "The tangent, radius, and distance from center form a right triangle where the distance is the hypotenuse.",
          "$r^2 + 4^2 = 5^2$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$r^2 + 16 = 25 \\\\ r^2 = 9 \\\\ r = 3 \\text{ cm}$"
      },
