      "question": "Two concentric circles are of radii $5 \\text{ cm}$ and $3 \\text{ cm}$. The length of the chord of the larger circle which touches the smaller circle is:",
      "answer": "(C)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Let the larger circle have radius $R=5$ and smaller have $r=3$.",
          "The chord is tangent to the inner circle, so the radius is perpendicular to the chord at the point of contact.",
          "This forms a right triangle with hypotenuse $5$ and one leg $3$.",
          "Find the half-length of the chord ($x$) using Pythagoras: $x^2 + 3^2 = 5^2$.",
          "Total length is $2x$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$x^2 + 9 = 25 \\\\ x^2 = 16 \\\\ x = 4 \\\\ \\text{Length} = 2x = 8 \\text{ cm}$"
      },
