      "question": "A quadrilateral $ABCD$ is drawn to circumscribe a circle. If $AB = 6 \\text{ cm}$, $BC = 7 \\text{ cm}$, and $CD = 4 \\text{ cm}$, then $AD$ is equal to:",
      "answer": "(D)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "For a quadrilateral circumscribing a circle, the sums of opposite sides are equal.",
          "$AB + CD = BC + AD$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$6 + 4 = 7 + AD \\\\ 10 = 7 + AD \\\\ AD = 3 \\text{ cm}$"
